<BaseLayout title="Camping" description="A two-day overnight camp at Tamarind Valley Collective — arrival, a hike to the sunset viewpoint, campfire, and a guided farm tour the next morning.">
  <PageHero eyebrow="Visit TVC" title="Overnight Camping" intro="Everything you need for a memorable camp — tented accommodation, home-cooked meals, and a hike to catch the sunset." />

  <section class="section wrapper">
    <h2>Day 1</h2>
    <p>Arrive at the farm post breakfast, refresh yourself with some juice made from the farm's produce. Check out your accommodation and settle in. Lunch is ready by 1:30pm — local cuisine, sourced from the farm as far as possible. Post-lunch, relax and wait for the temperature to come down. Have your tea/coffee and start the hike up to the Doddamma/Chikkamma temple, reaching the top around 4:30-5pm to watch the sun go down across the hills, then hike back to camp.</p>
    <p>Once back, enjoy some refreshments. Request a campfire and barbeque if you'd like — or skip it and let your conversation sync with the sound of crickets instead.</p>

    <h2>Day 2</h2>
    <p>Wake up early for a bird watching tour with Madhavan. Back at camp, have breakfast and relax, then go on a farm tour — the kitchen garden, the food forest, the check dams, the bunds and swales built to harvest water. Refresh with some juice or buttermilk afterward. Through the various discussions along the way, you'll pick up the principles of permaculture and how to harmonize with nature rather than fight it. Have lunch, then depart.</p>
    <p>You can extend your trip by a day for a forest appreciation walk, guided by our farm team, through the adjacent Thagatti Reserve Forest.</p>

    <div class="booking-cta">
      <p>Bookings for overnight camping are handled by our hospitality partner, Linger.</p>
      <a class="button" href="https://tamarindvalleycollective-farmstay.linger.in/the-campsite-tvc//" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Book via Linger</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

